<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">I haven't really noticed my company use it much, but the last company I worked for used it. I used to work for a car insurance company, and we built one of those "compare quotes from different companies but we are sure you will still pick us /wink" web sites. When submitting quote requests to other web sites, we tranfered the info in xml. It was easier to use, and basically, everyone followed the same standard, so you didn't have to guess their format.
<br />

<br />
That and, well, EQ uses it <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
