<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Based on what I've seen I think XML <B>IS</B> the de facto standard for internet based information exchange.<BR>
<br />
XML is like TCP/IP in that it handles the background manipulations and makes it easer to get things to talk to each other.  I think it's used many places where there is little point but over all it's usefull and it's going to stick around IMO.  However, you need to look past the hype as it does not do all that much.
<br />
<BR>PS: It has a lot of overhead but PC are fast so that's ok... 
<br />
 <img src="images/smiles/icon_rolleyes.gif" alt="icon_rolleyes.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
